title: Johnny Winter - LIVE: 1986-12-05 Poughkeepsie, NY [FLAC]
description:
Johnny Winter - 1986-12-05, The Chance, Poughkeepsie, NY, Aud/M, 90:51

LINEAGE: Sony Walkman (step below D6?) with 2 built-in condenser mics at the top; recorded at the Light Board > Maxell XL-II-S Tape (Dolby Off) > Sony TC-KA1ESA Tape Deck > Prodigy HD2 Soundcard > Cool Edit Pro > Wav > Trader's Little Helper > FLAC 8 > Adobe Audition > FLAC > Audacity > FLAC > Foobar2000 > FLAC 8

MASTERING NOTES (Adobe Audition CC 2014.2):
- All lossless transfers between programs & files
- Subsonic Rumble (<28Hz) Removal Throughout
- A few spots of manual rumble removal (beginning of tape, some spoken word throughout), generally <150 Hz for <1 sec
- VERY light EQ, EXTREMELY light hiss removal (to balance & naturalize sound); many hours were spent ensuring that this process did not affect the overall sound quality in a negative way.
- Light clipping repair
- No stereo widening effects added, since no suitable methods could be found
- Tracks split with Audacity 2.0.6, tagged with Foobar2000 v1.3.7
- 44100 Hz / 16 bit Lossless FLAC Audio for CD Burning
